 mid 12th-century writer refers to the place as ‘<i>Merthegrave, nunc</i> (now) <i>Belegrava</i>’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Hugh","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Hugues</i>, <i>Hugo</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>hug</i> ‘heart, mind, spirit’. It was originally a short form of various compound names containing this element. This was borne by the aristocracy of medieval France, adopted by the Normans, and introduced by them to Britain. It was consistently one of the most popular boys' names in the Middle Ages in England, but fell out of favour in the 16th century until it was revived in the 20th century. Little Hugh of Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":25,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":34,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":69,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugh de Belgrave was born about 1190, in Belgrave, Leicestershire, England, his father, Sir William de Belgrave, was 52 and his mother, Mrs. William de Belgrave, was 42. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Hugh de Belgrave."},"et":{"about 1190–Deceased":"umbes 1190–Surnud","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1195–Female":"1195–Surnud","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","about 1190":"umbes 1190","1224":"1224","1210":"1210","1140":"1140","1195":"1195","1150":"1150","Belgrave, Leicestershire, England":"Belgrave, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"about 1190–Deceased":"noin 1190–Kuollut","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1195–Female":"1195–Kuollut","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","about 1190":"noin 1190","1224":"1224","1210":"1210","1140":"1140","1195":"1195","1150":"1150","Belgrave, Leicestershire, England":"Belgrave, Leicestershire, England"},"fr":{"about 1190–Deceased":"environ 1190–Décédé","1190–Male":"1190–Décédé","1195–Female":"1195–Décédée","1210–Male":"1210–Décédé","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1150–Female":"1150–Décédée","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","about 1190":"environ 1190","1224":"1224","